    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>This year, the <a href="http://finviz.com/groups.ashx?g=industry&amp;v=210&amp;o=-perf1w" title="Top Performing Sectors - 8.3% Return on Tobacco Products Sector">tobacco industry has already shown a 8.3% return on investment</a>. We&rsquo;re looking for this trend to continue. One stock in this industry is Philip Morris - the largest cigarette manufacturer in America. Please observe the chart below:</p>

<h3 id="20170204-pm">PM</h3>


<p><a href="/images/blog/20170204/pm.png"><img src="/images/blog/20170204/pm.png" alt="PM - 2017-02-04 - Daily" /></a></p>

<p>PM is in a strong uptrend, breaking the 200MA and very far from the 20MA. We&rsquo;re now exploring the upper balance area set from 2016. Given the strong industry, how earnings has already passed, and that we&rsquo;re now in this upper range of balance and expect it to stay within this range, we&rsquo;re looking to collect premium in a favorable buy spot around the 200MA at $95.</p>

<p>Going over to the option chain and selecting the 95 Put strike in March:</p>

<p><a href="/images/blog/20170204/pmoc.png"><img src="/images/blog/20170204/pmoc.png" alt="PM - 2017-02-04 - Daily" /></a></p>

<p>With the bid at .34 and the ask at .41, we can look to sell this option for around .37. Essentially we could collect about $37 by March expiration. Hey, that covers the cost of about 6 or 7 cigarette packs. Although if you&rsquo;re smoking this much a month, you should really consider cutting back, for the sake of your health.</p>

